After performing substitute, Perl5Util.getMatch() always returns null. Thus the 
preMatch and postMatch are also nulls. See below test code:

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception
    {
        Perl5Util perl5Util = new Perl5Util();
        String resString = perl5Util.substitute("s/123/abc/", "ttt-123//");
        System.out.println("--- result String=" + resString);

        System.out.println("--- pre match='" + perl5Util.preMatch() + "'.");
        System.out.println("--- post match='" + perl5Util.postMatch() + "'.");

        org.apache.oro.text.regex.MatchResult matchRes = perl5Util.getMatch();
        if ( matchRes == null)
        {
            System.out.println("--- match result=null.");
        }
        else
        {
            System.out.println("--- match result='" + matchRes.toString() + 
"'.");
        }
    }
